org.eclipse.paho.mqttv5.client.internal

Class CommsCallback

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.paho.mqttv5.client.internal.CommsCallback
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable

    public class CommsCallback
extends Object
implements Runnable
    Bridge between Receiver and the external API. This class gets called by Receiver, and then converts the comms-centric MQTT message objects into ones understood by the external API.

      • connectionLost

        public void connectionLost(org.eclipse.paho.mqttv5.common.MqttException cause,
                           org.eclipse.paho.mqttv5.common.packet.MqttDisconnect message)
        This method is called when the connection to the server is lost. If there is no cause then it was a clean disconnect. The connectionLost callback will be invoked if registered and run on the thread that requested shutdown e.g. receiver or sender thread. If the request was a user initiated disconnect then the disconnect token will be notified.
        Parameters:
        cause - the reason behind the loss of connection.
        message - The MqttDisconnect packet sent by the server

      • removeMessageListener

        public void removeMessageListener(String topicFilter)
        Removes a Message Listener by Topic. If the Topic is null or incorrect, this function will return without making any changes. It will also attempt to find any subscription IDs linked to the same message listener and will remove them too.
        Parameters:
        topicFilter - the topic filter that identifies the Message listener to remove.

      • removeMessageListener

        public void removeMessageListener(Integer subscriptionId)
        Removes a Message Listener by subscription ID. If the Subscription Identifier is null or incorrect, this function will return without making any changes. It will also attempt to find any Topic Strings linked to the same message listener and will remove them too.
        Parameters:
        subscriptionId - the subscription ID that identifies the Message listener to remove.
